1. Download RStudio from https://www.rstudio.com/. Download R source code from https://cran.r-project.org/bin/macosx/. See detail on websites for installation.

2. For question, go to http://luthuli.cs.uiuc.edu/~daf/courses/LearningCourse/learning-book-21-jan-small.pdf. The question 2.5 is at the end  of chapter 2.

3. For dataset, go to https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/machine-learning-databases/adult/. Copy the whole content of adult.data and adult.test into a txt file and save as data.txt. You need to remove the first line in adult.test and all the . at the end of each line in adult.test.

4. All source files are in the patter hw2.R. 

5 Change setwd to your working directory and run the code. The code should print the accuracy and draw a graph.

